This paper is about dialogue systems, which are typically studied in the field of computational linguistics (cs.CL). The paper proposes a novel approach for learning dialogue systems that involves parameterizing different dialogue skills and selecting and combining them using attention mechanisms. This approach involves machine learning techniques, which are commonly studied in the fields of artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and machine learning (cs.LG). The paper also evaluates the proposed approach using experimental results, which suggests that it may fall under the sub-category of statistical learning (cs.SD). Finally, the paper discusses the potential applications of the proposed approach in assisting, informing, and entertaining humans, which suggests that it may also fall under the sub-category of human-computer interaction (cs.HC).
